  "prompt": "If you were born deaf, what language would you think in?",
  "response": "If a person is born deaf, they typically learn to think in the language they are most exposed to and comfortable with. For many deaf individuals, sign language becomes their primary mode of communication and thought. For example, if they learn American Sign Language (ASL), they might think in ASL. Thinking doesn't necessarily rely on a spoken or written language; it can be visual or conceptual. Deaf individuals may think in signs, images, and sometimes even in written words of a spoken language they have learned. Each person's experience can be unique, depending on their upbringing, education, and the languages they are exposed to.",
